Description: Secure Boot chain watchdog with native GNOME UI
 secureboot-watchdog detects degradation of the Secure Boot chain on
 systemd-boot machines (unsigned DKMS modules, missing MOK enrollment,
 SBAT revocations, unsigned EFI binaries, TPM PCR drift) and offers a
 polkit-elevated one-click fix via a native libadwaita app launched
 from a GNOME notification.
 .
 A root system service writes the chain status to
 /run/secureboot-monitor/status.json. A per-user path unit pops a
 notification when something needs repair; clicking it opens the
 GTK4/libadwaita repair app, which collects any required secret
 (LUKS passphrase or MOK enrollment password) and runs
 /usr/sbin/secureboot-fix through polkit.
